BelkinElago data exploratory analysis

Data set has been given by Danielle Sherman and the exploratory Analysis is shown below :

load data set

Belkin<-read.csv2("BelkinElagoComplete.csv")

Changing the Data type

{ r } Belkin$elevel <- as.factor(Belkin$elevel) Belkin$zipcode <- as.factor(Belkin$zipcode) df_status(Belkin) so Zipcode and elevel have been changed from numaric to factor

  • q_zeros: quantity of zeros (p_zeros: in percent)
  • q_inf: quantity of infinite values (p_inf: in percent)
  • q_na: quantity of NA (p_na: in percent)
  • type: factor or numeric
  • unique: quantity of unique values

Histogram of salary,age,credit(used for one continuous value)

library(ggplot2)
#salary
salary_his <- ggplot(Belkin,aes(x=salary))
salary_his + geom_histogram(binwidth=1000,color='red',fill='pink')

#age
age_his <- ggplot(Belkin,aes(x=age))
age_his + geom_histogram(binwidth=1,color='red',fill='pink')

#credit
credit_his <- ggplot(Belkin,aes(x=credit))
credit_his + geom_histogram(binwidth=1,color='red',fill='pink')

salary,age data is not normaly distributed but credit data is normaly distributed

#### Boxplot(used for discrete x and continuous y)

library(ggplot2)
#----------------------------------------zipcode vs salary------------------------#

belkin_box <- ggplot(data=Belkin,aes(x = factor(zipcode),y=salary)) 
belkin_box  + geom_boxplot()

belkin_box  + geom_boxplot(aes(fill = factor(brand)))#color seperated by brand

#------------------------------------zipcode vs credit----------------------------

belkin_box <- ggplot(data=Belkin,aes(x = factor(elevel),y=credit)) 
belkin_box  + geom_boxplot(aes(color=factor(brand)))+facet_grid(. ~ brand)#color seperated by brand

#------------------------------------age vs credit----------------------------

belkin_box <- ggplot(data=Belkin,aes(x = brand,y=car)) 
belkin_box  + geom_boxplot()#this graph does not mean anything

#-------------------------------------age vs brand----------------------------------#
belkin_box <- ggplot(data=Belkin,aes(x = brand,y=age)) 
belkin_box  + geom_boxplot(color="green")

#### 2d Hex Plot

library(ggplot2)
belkin_hex <- ggplot(data=Belkin,aes(x = credit,y=salary))
belkin_hex + geom_bin2d()

belkin_hex + geom_hex() + scale_fill_gradient(high='red',low='blue')

#----------------------Explaining patterns in credit status------------
ggplot(Belkin, mapping = aes(x=age,y=credit)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = salary)) + facet_wrap(~elevel)
